      <div xml:id="NA23-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu (ER: talaivi tuyar; EN, ET: talaivi; EV: talaiviyiṉ) āṟṟāmaiyai uṇarnta tōḻi (ET: talaimakaṉai) varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante who had perceived [HER] incapacity to bear [it] asked for marriage.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA23">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            toṭipaḻi maṟaittaliṟ ṟōḷuyn taṉavē</l>
<l>            vaṭikkoḷ kūḻai yāyamō ṭāṭali</l>
<l>            ṉiṭippu meyyatoṉ ṟuṭaittē kaṭikkoḷa</l>
<l>            vaṉṉai kākkun toṉṉalañ citaiyak</l>
<l>            kāṇṭoṟuṅ kaluḻta laṉṟiyu mīṇṭunīr </l>
<l>            muttuppaṭu parappiṟ koṟkai muṉṟuṟaic</l>
<l>            ciṟupā caṭaiya ceppūr neytaṟ</l>
<l>            ṟeṇṇīr malariṟ ṟolainta</l>
<l>            kaṇṇē kāmaṅ karappari yavvē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The shoulders lived while concealing the blame of the bracelets.</l>
<l rend="indent">While dancing with companions with styled short [hair],</l>
<l>the noise possesses one single body.</l>
<l>The eyes,</l>
<l rend="indent">lost like blossoms in the clear water of the blue waterlily creeping</l>
<l rend="indent">from the casket of little green leaves in the front ghat of Koṟkai</l>
<l rend="indent3">of an expanse where pearls come from the water here,</l>
<l rend="indent2">even apart from dimming each time they look</l>
<l rend="indent2">at the old innocence being wasted, that mother [was] guarding,</l>
<l rend="indent3">when bringing about protection,</l>
<l rend="indent3">it is difficult for them to hide desire.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
